Class MovementAnalyzer

  • java.lang.Object
    • Statistics.MovementAnalyzer
  • public class MovementAnalyzer
extends java.lang.Object
    MovementAnalyzer class generate AgentMovementData for each Agent, analyzes Agents movement, searching for collisions and calculating rate of collision risk between Agents

        public void addAgentMovementData​(java.lang.Integer agentID,
                                 java.lang.Double x1,
                                 java.lang.Double y1,
                                 java.lang.Double x2,
                                 java.lang.Double y2,
                                 java.lang.Double startTime,
                                 java.lang.Double finishTime,
                                 java.lang.Double agentRadius,
                                 java.lang.Boolean lastMovement)
        Creates AgentMovementData for an Agent for a specific time period of movement
        Parameters:
        agentID - Agent unique identifier
        x1 - x coordinate of starting point
        y1 - y coordinate of starting point
        x2 - x coordinate of finish point
        y2 - y coordinate of finish point
        startTime - time of beginning of movement
        finishTime - time of ending of movement
        agentRadius - parameter is needed to detect collision event and calculate collision risk
        lastMovement - if it is the last movement we should include the last point in SpaceTimeData collection
